: : Darkangel/DeathStar : :

Darkangel smiled behind his faceplate, taking pride in being named sub-commander. He winked at Dreadplague before she left, then quickly followed Commander Tyrael.

Darkangel: I take it you theory spell possible doom for us all?

DeathStar walked along side Dreadplague.

DeathStar: There was, but I&#39;m unsure of what has come of him.

Once outside the base, DeathStar changed to starfighter mode, flying towards the unknown signatures.


Nic &lt;Proudwing500k@...&gt; wrote:
Tyrael: I have a vague hypothesis... too fearsome to speak of here. I 
don&#39;t want to believe in it, but it seems to be the only one 
possible...

He stopped. His face was grave and his eyes showed fear. The Blue 
Phoenix, afraid?!

Tyrael: Dreadplague, Deathstar, go investigate the two signatures at 
these coordinates. If they are hostiles, do NOT engage. I want only 
data for now. Darkangel, I need your assistance and your advice. You 
are now officially my Second in command. Follow me please.

He left the room and went to the lab.

Dreadplague was wide eyed.

Dreadplague: Congratulations, Angel! We&#39;ll have to celebrate when I 
come back... (she had said that low enough that only Darkangel had 
heard) Come Deathstar. Let&#39;s do this and be done. Oh, by the way, 
wasn&#39;t there someone with you?


